Garner: CORNELL MUST BE
WORKING OFF A TIP

00:07.108 --> 00:09.008
THAT YOU
THREW AWAY EVIDENCE.

00:09.010 --> 00:09.742
YOU'RE FREE TO LEAVE.

00:09.744 --> 00:10.743
MEANING YOU FOUND ZIP.

00:10.745 --> 00:12.277
JOHN,
I STILL CAN'T PAY YOU.

00:12.279 --> 00:14.079
I GOT A CASHIER'S CHECK
FOR 25 GRAND LAST WEEK.

00:14.081 --> 00:15.647
I DON'T HAVE
THAT KIND OF MONEY.

00:15.649 --> 00:18.017
TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON,
OR I AM OUT OF HERE.

00:18.019 --> 00:19.151
GO!
WELL,
WHY ARE YOU FIGHTING?

00:19.153 --> 00:20.436
WE'RE LEAVING.
WHY? WHAT'S GOING ON?

00:20.437 --> 00:21.720
GO WITH YOUR MOM.
WE'RE GONNA FIGURE THIS OUT.

00:21.722 --> 00:23.756
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

00:23.757 --> 00:25.791
YOU DON'T REMEMBER GOING
TO JESS MURPHY'S THAT NIGHT?

00:25.793 --> 00:28.327
EITHER YOU'RE LYING
OR YOU HAD A BLACKOUT.

00:36.804 --> 00:39.071
[ FIRE CRACKLING ]

00:50.751 --> 00:53.485
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

00:53.487 --> 00:56.088
[ BIRD CAWING ]

01:00.127 --> 01:01.427
¶<i> ...NATIONS RISE</i> ¶

01:01.429 --> 01:03.062
Garner: ALL RIGHT,
WHICH ONE OF THESE DO YOU WANT?

01:03.064 --> 01:04.797
YOU WANT -- YOU WANT THIS ONE?
YOU READY FOR THIS ONE?

01:04.799 --> 01:06.432
COME ON, BUDDY.
OPEN THAT.

01:06.434 --> 01:08.200
OPEN THAT!
OPEN THAT!

01:08.202 --> 01:10.302
¶<i> WITH ANGELIC HOST PROCLAIM</i> ¶

01:10.304 --> 01:11.737
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
¶<i> CHRIST IS BORN IN BETHLEHEM</i> ¶

01:11.739 --> 01:13.205
WAIT. LET ME SEE.

01:14.241 --> 01:17.109
¶<i> HARK, THE HERALD ANGELS SING</i> ¶

01:17.111 --> 01:19.662
HANG ON.

01:19.663 --> 01:22.214
I GOT TO GO.
¶<i> GLORY TO THE NEWBORN KING</i> ¶

01:23.584 --> 01:26.485
MAN, I'M SORRY TO BOTHER YOU
ON CHRISTMAS.

01:26.487 --> 01:27.786
I-I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO.

01:27.788 --> 01:30.522
I KNOW. I KNOW.
CORNELL SENT ME THE VIDEO.

01:30.524 --> 01:32.291
HOW BAD IS IT?

01:32.293 --> 01:34.126
THEY'RE GONNA CHARGE YOU.

01:34.128 --> 01:35.627
[ Voice breaking ]
I'M GONNA BE ARRESTED?

01:35.629 --> 01:36.762
AH, TAKE IT EASY.

01:36.764 --> 01:38.197
I'M GONNA BE ARRESTED
FOR MURDER?

01:38.199 --> 01:39.598
NO, CALM DOWN.

01:39.600 --> 01:42.167
COME ON, BUDDY.
COME ON. RELAX.

01:43.804 --> 01:45.771
BREATHE.

01:45.772 --> 01:47.739
THEY'RE NOT GONNA DO IT TODAY,
OKAY?

01:47.741 --> 01:49.741
HEY, BEN, YOU BOUGHT
AT LEAST A WEEK

01:49.743 --> 01:51.844
WHEN YOU EXPOSED THE LEAK
IN THE CRIME LAB.

01:51.846 --> 01:53.312
LINDA FREEMAN'S ARREST

01:53.314 --> 01:55.814
NULLIFIES ALL THE EVIDENCE
TESTING SHE CONDUCTED.

01:55.816 --> 01:57.816
THEY THROW OUT
THE EVIDENCE?

01:57.818 --> 02:00.052
NO. THEY JUST HAVE TO
RETEST IT.

02:00.054 --> 02:01.887
THAT'S WHY SHE SHOWED US
THE VIDEO.

02:01.889 --> 02:05.524
I DON'T FOLLOW.
CORNELL CAN'T USE ANY OF THE
LEADS THAT CAME FROM THE LAB.

02:05.526 --> 02:07.626
SHE NEEDS ANOTHER AVENUE
TO GO AFTER YOU.

02:07.628 --> 02:09.895
AND THE VIDEO DOES THAT?

02:09.897 --> 02:11.397
IT DOES MORE THAN THAT.

02:11.398 --> 02:12.898
IT TELLS
THE PROSECUTION'S STORY --

02:12.900 --> 02:16.468
BEN CRAWFORD BRUTALLY MURDERED
HIS 5-YEAR-OLD SON.

02:16.470 --> 02:17.703
ONCE THE JURY SEES THAT,

02:17.705 --> 02:19.872
THEY'RE GONNA NEED
A CREDIBLE EXPLANATION

02:19.874 --> 02:22.441
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED THAT NIGHT
FROM YOUR OWN MOUTH.

02:22.443 --> 02:24.610
BUT I DON'T REMEMBER
WHAT HAPPENED THAT NIGHT.

02:24.612 --> 02:26.695
YOU BETTER REMEMBER QUICK

02:26.696 --> 02:28.779
BECAUSE IF YOU DON'T,
I CAN'T PUT YOU ON THE STAND.

02:28.782 --> 02:31.917
AND IF YOU CAN'T TESTIFY,
WE NEED TO TAKE A PLEA.

02:31.919 --> 02:33.785
YOU GOT TO
FIGURE THIS OUT.

02:33.787 --> 02:36.722
YOU GOT TO REMEMBER.

02:41.462 --> 02:44.496
[ BIRDS CAWING ]

02:48.169 --> 02:50.202
[ PARKING BRAKE CLICKS ]

02:52.673 --> 02:53.906
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

02:57.611 --> 02:59.611
[ SIGHS ]

02:59.613 --> 03:01.246
HOW YOU DOING?

03:01.248 --> 03:02.714
[ DOOR OPENS ]

03:02.716 --> 03:05.517
[ SIGHS ] JUST TRYING
TO GET THROUGH TODAY.

03:05.519 --> 03:07.136
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

03:07.137 --> 03:08.754
Nicole: THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR GOING TO THE TROUBLE.

03:08.756 --> 03:10.656
OH, PLEASE, STOP.
IT'S NO TROUBLE AT ALL.

03:10.658 --> 03:12.791
NOW, MY GRANDMOTHER USED TO SAY
THAT IT NEEDED TO SIT

03:12.793 --> 03:14.793
FOR AT LEAST TWO HOURS
BEFORE SHE SERVED IT,

03:14.795 --> 03:17.529
BUT FOR ME, IT'S AT LEAST
A HALF AN HOUR TO --

03:20.734 --> 03:22.768
UM, I HAVE TO GO.

03:22.770 --> 03:23.802
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

03:23.804 --> 03:25.270
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

03:26.574 --> 03:29.908
YOU CERTAINLY HAVE A WAY
WITH PEOPLE.

03:32.880 --> 03:35.948
SHE'S JUST TRYING
TO MAKE IT RIGHT.

03:35.950 --> 03:39.284
I DON'T KNOW IF SHE CAN.

03:39.286 --> 03:41.386
SHE'S MY SISTER.

03:41.388 --> 03:43.355
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
EXPLAIN YOURSELF TO ME.

03:45.893 --> 03:47.793
THERE'S SOMETHING
I NEED TO ASK YOU.

03:49.630 --> 03:52.297
IS THERE ANYTHING
YOU HAVEN'T TOLD ME

03:52.299 --> 03:53.599
ABOUT THE NIGHT TOM DIED?

03:53.601 --> 03:57.336
DO YOU THINK I'M
HIDING SOMETHING FROM YOU?

03:57.338 --> 03:58.537
NO, IT'S FOR MY LAWYER.

03:58.539 --> 04:00.706
UH, WE'RE JUST LOOKING
FOR SOMETHING --

04:00.708 --> 04:02.307
ANYTHING THAT COULD HELP.

04:02.309 --> 04:04.009
I'M SORRY.

04:05.813 --> 04:07.679
I'LL --
I'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

04:07.681 --> 04:09.014
WAIT, BEN.

04:09.016 --> 04:11.850
UM, THERE IS ONE THING,

04:11.852 --> 04:15.687
AND IT'S ONE OF THE REASONS WHY
I THOUGHT THAT SCOTT KILLED TOM.

04:15.689 --> 04:17.789
Nicole: JESS.

04:17.791 --> 04:19.258
I DON'T WANT TO BE LATE.

04:21.028 --> 04:22.361
YOU KNOW WHAT?

04:22.363 --> 04:25.364
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT'S PROBABLY NOTHING.

04:25.366 --> 04:27.399
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

04:28.836 --> 04:31.370
[ CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

04:31.372 --> 04:33.605
Boy: HEY, WAIT UP!
Boy #2: OKAY.

04:33.607 --> 04:34.606
[ CELLPHONE RINGING, VIBRATING ]

04:34.608 --> 04:36.508
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

04:37.945 --> 04:39.945
HEY, HONEY.
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

04:39.947 --> 04:41.813
HOW'S ABBY?

04:41.815 --> 04:42.881
YEAH?

04:42.883 --> 04:45.584
NAT, I CAN BARELY HEAR YOU.

04:45.586 --> 04:47.419
NATALIE:
When can we come home?

04:47.421 --> 04:48.854
IS SOMETHING WRONG?

04:48.856 --> 04:50.455
HOW ABOUT EVERYTHING?

04:50.457 --> 04:51.757
Abby's not talking,

04:51.759 --> 04:54.860
AND MOM IS OUT THERE
WITH MICHAEL AND HIS FRIENDS,

04:54.862 --> 04:56.928
LAUGHING LIKE
EVERYTHING'S NORMAL.

04:56.930 --> 04:59.931
I'M SORRY I'M PUTTING YOU GUYS
THROUGH THIS.

04:59.933 --> 05:02.934
WE HAVEN'T
OPENED OUR PRESENTS YET.

05:02.936 --> 05:04.836
WE'RE WAITING FOR YOU.

05:04.838 --> 05:08.507
WE'RE HAVING
A REALLY GOOD TIME.

05:08.509 --> 05:09.941
MOM'S RIGHT THERE,
ISN'T SHE?

05:09.943 --> 05:11.310
Yeah.

05:11.312 --> 05:13.545
EVERYTHING'S
TOTALLY AWESOME.

05:13.547 --> 05:14.880
HONEY.

05:14.882 --> 05:16.081
I'll see you soon,
okay?

05:16.083 --> 05:17.649
I'LL -- I'LL --
I'LL SET IT UP WITH MOM.

05:17.651 --> 05:19.518
UH, MOM WANTS
TO TALK TO YOU.

05:19.520 --> 05:20.686
Love you.

05:20.688 --> 05:22.554
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

05:25.659 --> 05:27.793
I NEED TO COME BY
AND GRAB SOME THINGS.

05:27.795 --> 05:29.628
Uh, I'll be here all day.

05:29.630 --> 05:30.796
You can come by
and get your stuff,

05:30.798 --> 05:32.464
AND I CAN WATCH THE GIRLS
OPEN THEIR GIFTS.

05:32.466 --> 05:33.465
WHENEVER YOU WANT.

05:33.467 --> 05:34.766
THAT DOESN'T WORK
FOR ME.

05:34.768 --> 05:35.834
Okay, I'll come to you.

05:35.836 --> 05:37.636
UH, JUST TELL ME
WHAT YOU NEED.

05:37.638 --> 05:39.471
JUST LET ME KNOW
WHEN YOU'LL BE OUT.

05:39.473 --> 05:40.939
CHRISTY, I'M TRYING
TO WORK WITH YOU HERE.

05:40.941 --> 05:42.708
I DON'T SEE WHY
YOU CAN'T DO THE SAME.

05:42.710 --> 05:44.676
I DON'T WANT TO SEE YOU.
That's your problem.

05:44.678 --> 05:46.545
I WANT TO SEE MY GIRLS.
IT'S CHRISTMAS.

05:46.547 --> 05:48.847
I'LL COME BY
ANOTHER TIME.

05:48.849 --> 05:50.949
GOD, CHRISTY,
BE REASONABLE!

05:50.951 --> 05:52.551
Ben, I'm asking you
politely.

05:52.553 --> 05:55.520
PLEASE, DO NOT COME HERE.

05:55.522 --> 05:56.521
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

05:56.523 --> 05:57.823
[ SIGHS ]

05:57.825 --> 05:58.824
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

05:58.826 --> 06:00.959
[ CELLPHONE THUDS ]

06:00.961 --> 06:03.095
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

06:03.097 --> 06:04.930
MERRY XMAS,
BI-OTCH!

06:04.932 --> 06:06.898
OKAY, THAT HAT...

06:06.900 --> 06:07.933
OW!

06:07.935 --> 06:08.834
YOU LIKE IT?

06:08.836 --> 06:10.602
WHO DID YOU
STEAL IT FROM?

06:10.604 --> 06:11.636
BITE ME.

06:11.638 --> 06:14.106
HEY,
I GOT YOU A PRESENT.

06:14.108 --> 06:16.375
I PUT A LITTLE THOUGHT
INTO IT,

06:16.377 --> 06:20.011
BUT I'LL BE COOL IF YOU
DON'T WANT TO KEEP IT.

06:22.816 --> 06:24.082
UH-OH.

06:24.084 --> 06:26.618
WHAT COULD IT BE?

06:26.620 --> 06:28.720
SOMETHING SPECIAL.

06:31.992 --> 06:33.125
IT WAS YOU?

06:33.127 --> 06:35.026
MERRY CHRISTMAS, BROTHER.
DUDE!

06:35.028 --> 06:37.095
YOU SAVED ME, MAN!

06:37.097 --> 06:38.130
YOU SAVED ME!

06:38.132 --> 06:40.465
WELL, I WOULDN'T
GO THAT FAR.

06:40.467 --> 06:42.467
NO, ALL RIGHT,
I TOTALLY DID.

06:42.469 --> 06:43.902
YOU OWE ME YOUR LIFE NOW.

06:43.904 --> 06:45.737
HOW THE HELL
DID YOU DO THIS?

06:45.739 --> 06:48.273
WELL, WHEN I HEARD

06:48.274 --> 06:50.808
THAT CHRISTY MIGHT HAVE NOTICED
YOU DITCHING IT IN THE WOODS,

06:50.811 --> 06:54.780
I REALIZED I HAD TO
DO SOMETHING, SO I GOT IT.

06:54.782 --> 06:57.449
THEN PLEASE TELL ME
THAT YOU WERE CAREFUL.

06:57.451 --> 06:59.818
OH, MAN,
I WAS LIKE A PANTHER.

06:59.820 --> 07:02.120
I WAS LIKE A FAT,
SEXY PANTHER.

07:02.122 --> 07:04.823
YOU KEPT ME OUT OF PRISON.

07:04.825 --> 07:06.825
YOU'D DO THE SAME FOR ME.

07:06.827 --> 07:09.728
ALL RIGHT, WE GOT TO GET RID
OF THIS NOW -- RIGHT NOW.

07:09.730 --> 07:11.196
NOW? OKAY.

07:11.198 --> 07:13.031
UH, WELL, THIS IS PERFECT

07:13.032 --> 07:14.865
'CAUSE EVERYONE'S WITH
THEIR FAMILIES, RIGHT?

07:17.104 --> 07:19.171
[ BIRD CAWING ]

07:21.475 --> 07:23.775
Dave: YOU SURE THIS IS
THE BEST SPOT FOR THIS, MAN?

07:23.777 --> 07:25.544
THERE'S NOBODY AROUND
FOR MILES,

07:25.546 --> 07:27.646
AND AFTER WHAT HAPPENED TO ME
OUT HERE,

07:27.648 --> 07:29.915
NO ONE WOULD EVER EXPECT
I'D COME HERE AGAIN.

07:29.917 --> 07:32.617
I HEARD
THERE WERE SNAKES HERE.

07:32.619 --> 07:34.052
ALL RIGHT,
HELP ME MOVE THIS THING.

07:34.054 --> 07:36.188
OH, GREAT.
IT'S THE ARK OF THE COVENANT.

07:36.190 --> 07:38.623
UM, REALLY?

07:38.625 --> 07:39.524
YEAH.

07:39.526 --> 07:40.625
GREAT.

07:40.627 --> 07:41.526
OKAY.

07:41.528 --> 07:43.628
OHH!

07:43.630 --> 07:44.996
[ GRUNTS ]

07:46.200 --> 07:48.934
[ COUGHS ]

07:50.871 --> 07:52.938
YOU SURE YOU WANT TO
GET RID OF THIS THING?

07:52.940 --> 07:53.939
[ SCOFFS ]

07:53.941 --> 07:55.507
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:55.509 --> 07:56.975
DO IT. DO IT.

07:58.579 --> 07:59.644
[ CLATTER ]

08:01.949 --> 08:02.948
[ SIGHS ]

08:06.887 --> 08:10.222
I JUST WANT TO STOP
AND SEE ABBY AND NAT.

08:10.224 --> 08:12.057
CHRISTY KNOWS WE'RE COMING,
RIGHT?

08:12.059 --> 08:15.894
HEY, MAN, THIS IS A WHOLE NEW
BALLGAME, ALL RIGHT?

08:15.896 --> 08:17.929
YOU GUYS AIN'T
ON THE SAME TEAM ANYMORE.

08:17.931 --> 08:19.798
I HAVE A RIGHT
TO SEE MY GIRLS.

08:19.800 --> 08:21.400
SURE, YOU DO,

08:21.401 --> 08:23.001
BUT THAT'S WHEN YOU WERE DEALING
WITH OLD CHRISTY, OKAY?

08:23.003 --> 08:24.769
THAT'S WHEN SHE WAS
SEMI-RATIONAL,

08:24.771 --> 08:25.937
WHEN SHE WAS MARRIED.

08:25.938 --> 08:27.104
THIS IS
"GETTING DIVORCED" CHRISTY.

08:27.107 --> 08:28.940
YOU HAVEN'T
MET HER YET, MAN.

08:28.942 --> 08:30.542
WHAT'S SHE GONNA DO?

08:30.544 --> 08:31.810
THAT'S THE POINT.

08:31.812 --> 08:33.011
YOU DON'T KNOW.

08:33.013 --> 08:33.912
I DON'T KNOW.

08:35.649 --> 08:37.516
I'M NOT GIVING UP
ON MY GIRLS.

08:37.518 --> 08:39.050
OF COURSE NOT, BUT LISTEN --
LISTEN -- LISTEN TO ME.

08:39.052 --> 08:41.820
CHRISTY HATES YOU NOW, OKAY?
SHE CAN'T THREATEN TO LEAVE YOU.

08:41.822 --> 08:43.655
YOU DON'T WANT MONEY.
YOU DON'T WANT SEX.

08:43.657 --> 08:45.023
WHAT ELSE COULD SHE
THREATEN YOU WITH?

08:45.025 --> 08:47.659
I'M GONNA SEE MY KIDS.

08:47.661 --> 08:50.595
BROTHER, THIS IS HOW EVERY
SINGLE EPISODE OF "COPS" STARTS.

08:50.597 --> 08:51.796
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

08:51.798 --> 08:53.632
I JUST KNEW
YOU WERE GONNA DO THIS.

08:53.634 --> 08:54.733
I'M NOT HERE FOR YOU.

08:54.735 --> 08:56.335
I DON'T CARE.
LEAVE.

08:56.336 --> 08:57.936
CHRISTY, IF YOU DON'T WANT
TO SEE ME, IT'S FINE.

08:57.938 --> 08:59.488
BUT IT'S CHRISTMAS,

08:59.489 --> 09:01.039
SO LET ME SPEND PART OF THE DAY
WITH ABBY AND NATALIE.

09:01.041 --> 09:02.924
YOU FORFEITED CHRISTMAS.

09:02.925 --> 09:04.808
HAVE YOUR LAWYER CALL MINE,
AND WE'LL TALK ABOUT NEW YEAR'S.

09:04.811 --> 09:06.945
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

09:06.947 --> 09:08.980
<i> YOU</i> DID THIS, BEN.

09:08.982 --> 09:11.550
AFTER I STOOD BY YOU.

09:11.552 --> 09:13.885
I TRIED
TO MAKE THINGS WORK.

09:13.887 --> 09:15.620
YOU STOLE THE BEST YEARS
OF MY LIFE,

09:15.622 --> 09:17.556
AND I AM NOT GONNA
LET YOU TAKE ANY MORE.

09:17.558 --> 09:20.025
AND THAT MAKES IT OKAY FOR YOU
TO HOLD MY KIDS HOSTAGE?

09:20.027 --> 09:21.977
THINK ABOUT THE GIRLS.

09:21.978 --> 09:23.928
I WILL NOT HAVE MY PARENTING
QUESTIONED BY A MAN WHO,

09:23.931 --> 09:27.132
UNTIL THREE WEEKS AGO, DIDN'T
KNOW HOW MANY CHILDREN HE HAD.

09:29.336 --> 09:30.869
YOU KNOW
I LOVE OUR GIRLS.

09:30.871 --> 09:32.938
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.

09:32.939 --> 09:35.006
YOU SAID YOU LOVED ME, AND
YOU LIED TO ME FOR SIX YEARS.

09:35.008 --> 09:37.108
YOU'RE REALLY GONNA USE OUR KIDS
TO GET YOUR REVENGE?!

09:37.110 --> 09:39.844
I'M PROTECTING THEM.

09:39.846 --> 09:41.913
YOU'RE A MURDER SUSPECT,
BEN.

09:41.915 --> 09:44.816
HOW DO YOU THINK THAT'S GONNA
LOOK TO A FAMILY-COURT JUDGE?

09:44.818 --> 09:46.184
YOU CAN'T KEEP ME
AWAY FROM THEM!

09:46.186 --> 09:47.986
THE POLICE CAN.

09:47.988 --> 09:49.287
HEY, GUYS.

09:49.289 --> 09:50.655
Michael:CHRISTY.
[ Ringing ]

09:50.657 --> 09:51.990
OPERATOR:
911. What's the emergency?

09:51.992 --> 09:53.758
CHRISTY.
GUYS.

09:53.760 --> 09:55.827
CHRISTY.
Hello?

09:56.163 --> 09:58.296
Can you hear me?

09:58.298 --> 09:59.831
Hello?

09:59.833 --> 10:00.999
[ SOBBING ]

10:01.001 --> 10:02.667
PLEASE COME INSIDE.

10:02.669 --> 10:06.137
This emergency call is now being
declared failure to respond.

10:06.139 --> 10:07.706
For your safety,
I'm dispatching units.

10:07.708 --> 10:08.807
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

10:10.177 --> 10:11.176
I'M SORRY.

10:13.013 --> 10:14.112
ABBY.

10:14.114 --> 10:15.347
Are you there?
YES, HELLO?

10:15.349 --> 10:16.982
Who's this?
YES, MICHAEL JAMES.

10:16.984 --> 10:18.316
NO, THERE'S NO NEED
FOR POLICE.

10:20.053 --> 10:21.186
BEER?

10:21.188 --> 10:22.854
NO, THANKS.

10:27.861 --> 10:29.327
MAN,
THANKS FOR TRYING --

10:29.329 --> 10:31.863
NO, YOU KNOW WHAT?
SKIP IT, MAN.

10:31.865 --> 10:34.666
I CAN STILL
HEAR MY PARENTS

10:34.668 --> 10:36.901
HURLING OBSCENITIES AT EACH
OTHER LIKE IT WAS YESTERDAY.

10:36.903 --> 10:38.870
I NEVER WANTED THE GIRLS
TO SEE THAT.

10:38.872 --> 10:41.006
THE GIRLS ARE GONNA GET HURT
NO MATTER WHAT.

10:41.008 --> 10:43.775
I JUST DON'T KNOW
HOW I GOT HERE.

10:43.777 --> 10:47.879
IT'S GONNA BE FINE...
EVENTUALLY.

10:47.881 --> 10:50.148
NO, I MEAN,
CHRISTY'S RIGHT.

10:50.150 --> 10:53.051
HOW -- HOW CAN I
GET JOINT CUSTODY

10:53.053 --> 10:55.353
WHEN I'VE GOT A MURDER TRIAL
HANGING OVER MY HEAD?

10:55.355 --> 10:58.957
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
DID I MISS YOUR ARREST?

10:58.959 --> 11:00.959
MY LAWYER SAYS
THAT IF I CAN'T REMEMBER

11:00.961 --> 11:02.961
WHAT HAPPENED THAT NIGHT,
I'VE GOT TO PLEAD GUILTY.

11:05.032 --> 11:08.133
WELL, THEN YOU NEED
A NEW LAWYER, MAN.

11:08.135 --> 11:10.902
DAVE, IF I GO TO TRIAL, THE
DEATH PENALTY'S ON THE TABLE.

11:13.206 --> 11:15.473
THE NIGHT TOM DIED,

11:15.474 --> 11:17.741
I CAN'T REMEMBER ANYTHING
AFTER THE FIGHT WITH CHRISTY.

11:17.744 --> 11:20.311
THAT WAS A ROUGH ONE,
WASN'T IT?

11:20.313 --> 11:22.263
BUT THAT'S ON YOU, MAN.

11:22.264 --> 11:24.214
I MEAN [SCOFFS] IT SAYS
RIGHT THERE IN THE HANDBOOK,

11:24.217 --> 11:27.986
"IF THE WOMAN ASKS YOU IF YOU
CHEATED, YOU JUST SAY NO."

11:33.794 --> 11:36.027
YOU OKAY?

11:36.897 --> 11:38.430
CHRISTY.

11:41.802 --> 11:44.069
ARE YOU CHEATING ON ME?

11:46.073 --> 11:47.906
WHERE IS THIS
COMING FROM?

11:49.976 --> 11:52.143
ANSWER THE QUESTION.

11:53.213 --> 11:55.714
NO. I'M...

11:55.716 --> 11:56.881
I'M NOT.

11:56.883 --> 11:58.483
YOU'VE NEVER CHEATED?

12:00.387 --> 12:01.786
WHY DO YOU EVEN CARE?

12:01.788 --> 12:03.722
YOU HAVEN'T TOUCHED ME
IN MONTHS.

12:03.724 --> 12:06.391
YOU DON'T REACH FOR ME,
EITHER.

12:06.393 --> 12:08.860
THAT'S WHY I THINK
THERE'S SOMEONE ELSE.

12:08.862 --> 12:11.162
OKAY, LIKE WHO?

12:11.164 --> 12:13.298
LIKE JESS.

12:15.469 --> 12:17.335
[ SIGHS ]

12:19.039 --> 12:23.875
IT WAS JUST -- JUST ONCE
Y-YEARS AGO. IT WAS --
SHE LIVES RIGHT THERE
ACROSS THE STREET.

12:23.877 --> 12:26.010
I DIDN'T MEAN FOR IT
TO HAPPEN.

12:26.012 --> 12:27.946
THAT MAKES IT OKAY?

12:27.948 --> 12:31.349
SHE'S BEEN IN AND OUT
OF THIS HOUSE, BEN.

12:31.351 --> 12:34.052
NATALIE WATCHES HER SON.

12:34.054 --> 12:35.820
CHRISTY, I SHOULD HAVE TOLD YOU.
I JUST DIDN'T WANT TO HURT --

12:35.822 --> 12:37.188
"SHOULD HAVE TOLD."
DON'T YOU DARE!

12:37.190 --> 12:38.757
"SHOULD HAVE TOLD."

12:38.759 --> 12:41.993
YOU HAVE SO LITTLE RESPECT
FOR ME

12:41.995 --> 12:44.062
THAT YOU DON'T EVEN HAVE
THE COMMON DECENCY

12:44.064 --> 12:46.064
TO LET ME KNOW
WHEN I AM BEING HUMILIATED.

12:46.066 --> 12:47.999
CHRISTY, I'M SORRY.

12:48.001 --> 12:49.534
YOU NEED TO GO.

12:49.536 --> 12:51.369
WHERE?
WHERE AM I SUPPOSED TO GO?

12:51.371 --> 12:53.271
GO TO YOUR GIRLFRIEND'S.

12:53.273 --> 12:56.040
SCOTT'S GONE.
YOU CAN JUST MOVE RIGHT IN.

12:56.042 --> 12:57.942
I DON'T -- I DON'T WANT
TO BE WITH JESS! THAT'S --

12:57.944 --> 13:00.278
IF YOU DON'T GET OUT
RIGHT NOW,

13:00.280 --> 13:03.081
I WILL PACK UP THE GIRLS
AND LEAVE TONIGHT!

13:05.986 --> 13:07.919
GET OUT!

13:12.359 --> 13:15.059
I STILL CAN'T FIGURE OUT
WHY SHE SUDDENLY ASKED.

13:15.061 --> 13:16.528
THANKSGIVING.

13:16.530 --> 13:18.062
WE WATCHED THE GAME.

13:18.064 --> 13:20.431
WE PLAYED TOUCH FOOTBALL
IN THE STREET.

13:20.433 --> 13:23.968
YEAH, AND CHRISTY
PAID ATTENTION.

13:23.970 --> 13:25.503
CHRISTY
WASN'T EVEN PLAYING.

13:25.505 --> 13:29.908
OH, NO, BUT SHE NOTICED,
MR. TWO-HAND TOUCH --

13:29.910 --> 13:33.411
ALL THE TICKLY TACKLES
AND THE EXTRA HIGH FIVES

13:33.413 --> 13:37.182
AND THE SILLY GRINS, YOU KNOW,
LONGING LOOKS.

13:37.184 --> 13:40.518
I DON'T GIVE JESS
LONGING LOOKS.

13:40.520 --> 13:42.287
HOW DO YOU KNOW
IF YOU CAN'T SEE YOUR OWN FACE?

13:42.289 --> 13:44.022
'CAUSE THERE WAS NOTHING
TO SEE.

13:44.024 --> 13:45.290
I SAW IT,
AND I'M AN IDIOT.

13:45.292 --> 13:47.926
LOOK, I GET IT, MAN.

13:47.928 --> 13:51.462
JESS IS SMOKING-HOT.
SHE'S SUPER COOL.

13:51.464 --> 13:53.932
SHE LISTENS TO YOU.
SHE DON'T LOOK DOWN ON YOU.

13:53.934 --> 13:56.935
AND IT SEEMS LIKE
SHE GENUINELY LIKES YOU.

13:56.937 --> 13:59.304
I MEAN, THAT'S --
THAT'S NICE.

13:59.306 --> 14:04.542
THERE'S NOTHING NICE ABOUT
MY FAMILY FALLING APART.

14:04.544 --> 14:08.046
WHATEVER IT WAS WITH JESS,
IT WASN'T REAL.

14:08.048 --> 14:09.981
CHRISTY WAS.

14:09.983 --> 14:12.150
YEAH, WELL,
CHRISTY MIGHT HAVE LOVED YOU,

14:12.152 --> 14:14.619
BUT SHE NEVER LIKED YOU.

14:17.057 --> 14:20.491
MAYBE I'M JUST
BETTER OFF ALONE.

14:20.493 --> 14:22.177
OH, BUDDY, I LOVE YOU,

14:22.178 --> 14:23.862
BUT YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT THE HELL
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

14:27.334 --> 14:29.100
MAN, YOU'RE NOT ALONE.
YOU GOT ME.

14:29.102 --> 14:32.003
NOT FOR LONG.

14:33.473 --> 14:36.040
I GOT TO
TELL YOU SOMETHING.

14:36.042 --> 14:38.977
I SHOULD HAVE TOLD YOU
A LONG TIME AGO,

14:38.979 --> 14:41.479
BUT I DIDN'T KNOW
HOW TO DO IT.

14:41.481 --> 14:45.016
[ SIGHS ]

14:45.018 --> 14:47.285
DAVE?

14:47.287 --> 14:48.987
UM...

14:48.989 --> 14:52.523
YOU WERE GOING THROUGH SO MUCH,
YOU KNOW, AND -- AND...

14:52.525 --> 14:57.228
JUST TRUST THAT I WANTED TO COME
CLEAN SO MANY TIMES, ALL RIGHT?

14:57.230 --> 14:59.530
YOU GOT TO BELIEVE ME.

14:59.532 --> 15:01.332
I COULDN'T.

15:01.334 --> 15:04.335
I JUST -- I C--

15:04.337 --> 15:06.137
WHAT DID YOU DO?

15:07.540 --> 15:08.539
DAVE, WHAT DID YOU DO?

15:12.112 --> 15:14.979
DAVE, WHAT DID YOU DO?!
JUST SAY IT!

15:14.981 --> 15:17.165
OKAY.

15:17.166 --> 15:19.350
UH...NIGHT OF THE BIG FIGHT
YOU HAD WITH CHRISTY,

15:19.352 --> 15:22.053
YOU CAME OUT TO THE GUESTHOUSE
TO COME TALK TO ME.

15:22.055 --> 15:24.022
I'VE KNOWN YOU
A LONG, LONG TIME.

15:24.024 --> 15:26.057
I AIN'T NEVER SEEN YOU
LIKE THAT BEFORE.

15:26.059 --> 15:26.958
LIKE WHAT?

15:26.960 --> 15:28.126
OH, BUDDY.

15:28.128 --> 15:31.029
YOU WERE -- YOU WERE
IN A REALLY BAD WAY.

15:31.031 --> 15:33.231
YOU WERE JUST REALLY DARK,
YOU KNOW?

15:33.233 --> 15:35.166
I GOT CONCERNED.

15:35.168 --> 15:37.035
SO WHEN YOU SAID, "I GOT TO
GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE,"

15:37.037 --> 15:39.604
WE JUST WENT TO
THE CLOSEST PLACE THAT WAS OPEN.

15:39.606 --> 15:41.640
HEY!

15:41.641 --> 15:43.675
ANOTHER ROUND OVER HERE.
ME AND THIS GUY.

15:43.677 --> 15:45.043
WOULD YOU DRAIN THAT?

15:45.045 --> 15:46.544
COME ON, YOU MANIAC.

15:46.546 --> 15:48.379
I DIDN'T KNOW
IT WAS POSSIBLE,

15:48.380 --> 15:50.213
BUT I THINK ALCOHOL'S ACTUALLY
MAKING ME MORE DEPRESSED.

15:50.216 --> 15:52.116
REMEMBER BACK IN THE DAY
HOW WE USED TO

15:52.118 --> 15:54.519
JUST SMOKE A BIG OLD BOWL
AND JUST FORGET ABOUT IT?

15:54.521 --> 15:57.956
YEAH, WE'D LITERALLY
FORGET EVERYTHING --

15:57.958 --> 16:00.158
OUR NAMES, ADDRESSES.

16:00.160 --> 16:02.226
I MISS THE GOOD OLD DAYS.

16:02.228 --> 16:07.131
YOU KNOW, B.C. --
BEFORE CHRISTY.

16:08.468 --> 16:10.735
I DON'T THINK WEED
WOULD MAKE A DENT.

16:10.737 --> 16:12.103
MAYBE
A HORSE TRANQUILIZER.

16:12.105 --> 16:14.039
YOU KNOW WHAT?

16:14.040 --> 16:15.974
I'M NEVER GONNA LET YOU GET
NEAR IT BECAUSE IT'S POISON.

16:15.976 --> 16:19.043
AH, THANK YOU,
MY GOOD MAN.

16:19.045 --> 16:20.211
THANK YOU.

16:20.213 --> 16:23.114
NOW, YOU FINISH THAT
AND DRINK THAT.

16:24.050 --> 16:26.451
I'M GONNA GO GET RID
OF THE LAST ROUND.

16:26.453 --> 16:28.019
I'LL BE BACK.

16:28.021 --> 16:31.022
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

16:31.024 --> 16:32.523
[<i> MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING</i> ]

16:48.041 --> 16:49.440
[ PILLS RATTLE ]

16:56.016 --> 16:57.582
YOU DRUGGED ME?!

16:57.584 --> 16:59.083
I WAS TRYING
TO HELP YOU.

16:59.085 --> 17:00.935
BY DRUGGING ME?!

17:00.936 --> 17:02.786
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU WERE GONNA
HAVE SUCH A STRONG REACTION!

17:02.789 --> 17:07.158
OH, MY GOD, MAN.
WELL, THAT EXPLAINS IT!

17:07.160 --> 17:10.261
WELL, NOW, YOU'RE AN IDIOT!
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?!

17:10.263 --> 17:12.663
[ SIGHS ]
THEY'RE USUALLY HARMLESS.

17:12.665 --> 17:14.432
THE DOCTOR
THAT GIVES THEM TO ME,

17:14.434 --> 17:16.367
HE SAYS THEY'RE FOR STRESS,
YOU KNOW?

17:16.369 --> 17:17.802
I'M NOT SUPPOSED TO DRINK
WITH THEM,

17:17.804 --> 17:19.203
BUT NOTHING BAD
HAS EVER HAPPENED.

17:19.205 --> 17:21.322
I NEVER BLACKED OUT
FROM IT.

17:21.323 --> 17:23.440
YOU GOT, LIKE, METABOLISM LIKE
A HUMMINGBIRD OR SOMETHING, MAN.

17:23.443 --> 17:27.111
LOOK, IT'S TOTALLY MY FAULT.

17:27.113 --> 17:29.514
I'M SO, SO SORRY.

17:29.516 --> 17:31.549
YOU DIDN'T THINK THAT MAYBE
YOU SHOULD HAVE TOLD ME?!

17:31.551 --> 17:34.052
HOW MANY TIMES
DID YOU HEAR ME FREAKING OUT

17:34.054 --> 17:36.721
BECAUSE I COULDN'T REMEMBER
WHAT HAPPENED THAT NIGHT?!

17:39.092 --> 17:42.326
[ Crying ]
YOU GOT TO UNDERSTAND, OKAY?

17:42.328 --> 17:44.362
THE THING WITH NAT --

17:44.364 --> 17:46.164
YOU SAID BEING MY FRIEND

17:46.166 --> 17:49.734
WAS THE WORST MISTAKE
YOU EVER MADE IN YOUR LIFE.

17:49.736 --> 17:53.571
AND I DIDN'T EVEN
DO ANYTHING.

17:53.573 --> 17:56.507
SO I GOT SCARED.

17:56.509 --> 17:59.544
I GOT REALLY SCARED.

17:59.546 --> 18:01.279
I DIDN'T KNOW
HOW TO TELL YOU.

18:02.248 --> 18:04.549
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

18:04.551 --> 18:07.318
YOU GOT TO FORGIVE ME.

18:09.122 --> 18:13.291
I GUESS I CAN KIND OF SEE
WHY YOU DID IT, BUT...

18:13.293 --> 18:16.160
IT WAS A TERRIBLE
DECISION, MAN.

18:16.162 --> 18:19.297
IT WAS THE WORST DECISION
I'VE EVER MADE IN MY LIFE.

18:22.102 --> 18:24.268
ALL RIGHT.

18:26.139 --> 18:27.305
[ SIGHS ]

18:27.307 --> 18:30.274
THAT'S IT?
"ALL RIGHT"?

18:30.276 --> 18:32.276
YOU DON'T WANT TO -- YOU DON'T
WANT TO BEAT ME TO DEATH

18:32.278 --> 18:33.478
WITH MY OWN ARM
OR SOMETHING?

18:33.480 --> 18:36.848
DUDE, YOU'RE MY...
BEST FRIEND.

18:36.850 --> 18:39.884
YOU'RE MY ONLY FRIEND.

18:39.886 --> 18:41.752
YOUR HEART
WAS IN THE RIGHT PLACE,

18:41.754 --> 18:43.621
EVEN IF YOUR HEAD
WAS UP YOUR ASS.

18:43.623 --> 18:45.756
I --

18:45.758 --> 18:48.126
YOU'RE, LIKE, THE GREATEST
FRIEND A GUY'S EVER HAD.

18:49.729 --> 18:51.262
[ Sobbing ]
I'M SO SORRY!

18:51.264 --> 18:54.165
I'M SO SORRY.
YOU FORGIVE ME, MAN?

18:54.167 --> 18:55.733
ALL RIGHT, LET'S --

18:55.735 --> 18:58.202
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S MOVE ON.

18:58.204 --> 19:02.340
HELP ME REMEMBER WHAT HAPPENED
THE NIGHT TOM DIED.

19:03.743 --> 19:06.210
[ CLAPS HANDS ]
YOU WEREN'T YOURSELF.

19:06.212 --> 19:08.246
HOW?

19:08.248 --> 19:09.480
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

19:09.482 --> 19:12.183
WELL, UH, YOU KNOW,
MOST PEOPLE WOULD SAY

19:12.185 --> 19:14.252
THAT YOU'RE COOL AND CALM
AND COLLECTED

19:14.254 --> 19:17.655
AND SOMETIMES ALOOF.

19:17.657 --> 19:19.924
NOT THAT NIGHT.

19:19.926 --> 19:24.829
ALL I'M SAYING IS THE
INSTITUTION OF MARRIAGE STARTED

19:24.831 --> 19:26.864
WHEN LIFE EXPECTANCY WAS 40.

19:26.866 --> 19:29.901
40?!

19:29.903 --> 19:31.702
YOU'D HAVE BEEN DEAD.

19:31.704 --> 19:34.605
THINK ABOUT THAT.
IT'S CRAZY.

19:34.607 --> 19:36.407
IT'S A SHAM, GENTLEMEN.

19:36.409 --> 19:38.376
IT'S A TOTAL SHAM!

19:38.378 --> 19:39.510
OH, MY GOD.

19:39.512 --> 19:41.713
WHATEVER.

19:41.714 --> 19:43.915
UM, YEAH, YOU KNOW, YOU JUST --
YOU STAY FOR THE KIDS.

19:43.917 --> 19:44.849
YOU DON'T CUT AND RUN.

19:44.851 --> 19:46.817
WHO DOES THAT?

19:46.819 --> 19:49.320
PONYTAIL, WHO DOES THAT?

19:49.322 --> 19:50.421
I DON'T.

19:50.423 --> 19:52.190
MY --
NOT WHERE I COME FROM.

19:54.894 --> 19:56.827
[ DAVE LAUGHS ]
PEOPLE CHANGE.

19:56.829 --> 19:57.828
RIGHT, DAVE?

19:57.830 --> 19:59.697
YEAH, DUDE. YEAH.

19:59.699 --> 20:00.965
OH, BABY.
OH, REALLY?

20:00.967 --> 20:02.767
LET'S SAY
YOU TWO GET MARRIED.

20:02.769 --> 20:03.901
LET'S NOT.

20:03.903 --> 20:05.536
AND THEN
ALL OF A SUDDEN,

20:05.538 --> 20:07.772
DAVE BECOMES
A COMPLETELY DIFFERENT PERSON.

20:07.774 --> 20:09.224
THEN WHAT?

20:09.225 --> 20:10.675
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU STAY FOR THE KIDS.

20:10.677 --> 20:13.678
AND YOU HOPE AND YOU PRAY
THAT DAVE CAN GO BACK

20:13.680 --> 20:16.747
TO BEING THAT GUY HE WAS
WHEN YOU FIRST MET HIM.

20:16.749 --> 20:20.885
BUT IF HE BECOMES AN ICY,
CONTROLLING BITCH...

20:20.887 --> 20:22.587
OH.

20:22.589 --> 20:23.754
...THEN YOU GOT TO
LIE TO YOURSELF.

20:23.756 --> 20:25.573
YOU GOT TO STAY
FOR THE KIDS.

20:25.574 --> 20:27.391
YOU GOT TO TELL YOURSELF,
"YEAH, HE COULD CHANGE.

20:27.393 --> 20:28.793
"HE COULD GO BACK
TO BEING THAT PERSON

20:28.795 --> 20:30.678
THAT I FELL IN LOVE WITH."

20:30.679 --> 20:32.562
[ Laughing ] WAIT A MINUTE.
WAIT A MINUTE.

20:32.565 --> 20:34.332
AM I RIGHT?
YEAH, DUDE.

20:34.334 --> 20:37.301
RIGHT?
[ LAUGHS ]

20:37.303 --> 20:39.537
I DON'T --

20:39.539 --> 20:40.538
[ GRUNTS ]

20:40.540 --> 20:41.906
YOU'LL SEE.
MARK MY WORDS.

20:41.908 --> 20:44.008
MARK MY WORDS!

20:44.010 --> 20:45.776
OH, MY GOD.

20:45.778 --> 20:47.278
HEY, HEY.
WHERE YOU GOING?

20:47.280 --> 20:48.646
LET ME GO.
HUH?

20:48.648 --> 20:50.348
IT'S, LIKE,
EXACTLY WHAT I MEAN.

20:50.350 --> 20:51.949
I GO GET YOU PEANUTS,
LIKE YOU ASK,

20:51.951 --> 20:55.453
AND THEN ONE MISTAKE, AND YOU
JUST GIVE UP AND WALK AWAY.

20:55.455 --> 20:57.622
YOU NEED TO
LET GO OF MY ARM!

20:57.624 --> 20:58.522
[ PEOPLE GASP ]

20:58.524 --> 20:59.957
HEY, HEY!

20:59.959 --> 21:01.859
TIME TO GET YOU HOME.

21:01.861 --> 21:03.327
HEY.

21:03.329 --> 21:05.396
Dave: OH, BUDDY.
I'M SORRY.

21:05.398 --> 21:06.931
I'M GONNA FIX IT.

21:06.933 --> 21:08.466
I GOT TO FIX IT.

21:08.468 --> 21:09.800
OKAY, ALL RIGHT.
I'M GONNA FIX IT.

21:09.802 --> 21:12.503
OKAY,
WE'RE GONNA FIX IT.

21:12.505 --> 21:14.472
LET'S GO. COME ON.

21:14.474 --> 21:15.940
SORRY.

21:15.942 --> 21:18.042
I SCOOPED YOU UP
AND I PUT YOU IN A CAB

21:18.044 --> 21:20.044
AND I SENT YOU HOME,
AND THAT WAS IT.

21:20.046 --> 21:22.980
AND YOU DIDN'T THINK THAT MAYBE
YOU SHOULD COME HOME WITH ME?

21:22.982 --> 21:24.649
WHAT'S THE WORST
THAT COULD HAPPEN?

21:24.651 --> 21:27.785
HE TOOK YOU HOME.
YOU GOT IN BED, RIGHT?

21:27.787 --> 21:29.520
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

21:29.522 --> 21:32.790
THERE WAS A PROBLEM, MAN.
THE VIDEO'S THE PROBLEM.

21:32.792 --> 21:34.625
WHAT VIDEO?

21:34.627 --> 21:36.927
CORNELL SHOWED IT TO ME
LAST NIGHT.

21:36.929 --> 21:38.496
IT'S FROM THE TAXI.

21:38.498 --> 21:41.966
YOU SEE ME GET OUT AND WALK
DIRECTLY TO JESS' HOUSE.

21:41.968 --> 21:45.069
OH, GOD, NO.

21:45.071 --> 21:48.306
I-I-I WAS DRUNK.
I WAS DRUGGED.

21:48.308 --> 21:52.343
AND I WAS VIOLENT,
AND I DIDN'T GO HOME.

21:52.345 --> 21:54.612
I COULD HAVE DONE ANYTHING
THAT NIGHT.

21:58.685 --> 22:00.751
NO WAY.
NO WAY. NO WAY, MAN!

22:00.753 --> 22:01.886
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

22:01.888 --> 22:03.821
I DON'T CARE IF YOU'RE ON PCP,
KETAMINE,

22:03.823 --> 22:06.824
AND -- AND TANNIS ROOT,
YOU'RE NOT GONNA KILL ANYBODY!

22:06.826 --> 22:09.327
IF I WAS DRUNK, SURE.

22:09.329 --> 22:11.929
BUT ON DRUGS, MAN, WHO KNO--
I MEAN --

22:11.931 --> 22:13.931
YOU COULD HAVE BEEN
WHACKED OUT OF YOUR TREE,

22:13.933 --> 22:15.533
BUT YOU DON'T HAVE A REASON,
RIGHT?

22:15.535 --> 22:16.801
WHAT'S YOUR MOTIVE?

22:16.803 --> 22:18.069
EXACTLY.

22:18.071 --> 22:19.770
WHAT IF
I WENT TO SEE TOM

22:19.772 --> 22:22.573
AND HE WALKED AWAY FROM ME
LIKE THAT WOMAN AT THE BAR?

22:22.575 --> 22:23.941
OR HE COULD --
MAYBE IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

22:23.943 --> 22:25.393
TOM WOULD HAVE LET ME IN.

22:25.394 --> 22:26.844
[ SNAPS FINGERS ]
YOU DON'T GOT YOUR FLASHLIGHT.

22:26.846 --> 22:28.546
WHAT?
LISTEN.

22:28.548 --> 22:30.414
YOU GET OUT OF THE CAB.
YOU GO TO JESS'.

22:30.416 --> 22:31.949
YOU DON'T HAVE
YOUR FLASHLIGHT!

22:31.951 --> 22:33.384
YEAH, BUT I COULD HAVE...

22:33.386 --> 22:35.453
STOPPED AND PICKED IT UP
ON THE WAY TO THE WOODS.

22:35.455 --> 22:36.621
WHO KNOWS, MAN?!

22:36.622 --> 22:37.788
I DON'T REMEMBER
WHAT HAPPENED THAT NIGHT!

22:37.790 --> 22:40.891
LET'S RETRACE.

22:40.893 --> 22:46.063
NOW, IF WE'RE GONNA DO THIS
MY WAY, YOU GOT TO COMMIT 100%.

22:46.065 --> 22:50.868
WHENEVER I LOSE ANYTHING, WHICH,
AS YOU KNOW, IS QUITE OFTEN,

22:50.870 --> 22:53.571
I GO UNDERCOVER AS MYSELF,
OKAY?

22:53.573 --> 22:54.905
AND IT'S A VERY SERIOUS
BUSINESS.

22:54.907 --> 22:57.975
WE ARE RE-CREATING THE NIGHT
HERE, OKAY?

22:57.977 --> 23:02.480
SAME PLACES, SAME MUSIC,
SAME FOOD, SAME EVERYTHING.

23:02.482 --> 23:03.614
YOU WITH ME?

23:03.616 --> 23:05.683
THAT WORKS FOR YOU?
YEAH.

23:05.685 --> 23:07.285
LIKE FIVE TIMES
OUT OF EIGHT,

23:07.286 --> 23:08.886
I REMEMBER EXACTLY HALF
OF EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENS.

23:10.089 --> 23:11.822
YOU GOT A BETTER IDEA?

23:14.894 --> 23:16.627
¶<i> ROCK, RUDOLPH, ROCK</i> ¶

23:16.629 --> 23:18.429
¶<i> ROLL, RUDOLPH, ROLL</i> ¶

23:18.431 --> 23:19.563
[<i> INDISTINCT SINGING</i> ]

23:24.937 --> 23:29.140
¶<i> NOW, SANTA SAID TO RUDOLPH,</i>
<i> "KNOW I OWE YOU A LOT"</i> ¶

23:29.142 --> 23:31.409
NO, NO, NO, NO.

23:31.411 --> 23:33.411
THESE TWO.
THIS IS WHERE WE WERE.

23:35.148 --> 23:38.482
ANY TROUBLE LIKE LAST TIME,
AND I CALL THAT COP.

23:38.484 --> 23:39.917
I HAVE HER CARD
RIGHT HERE.

23:39.919 --> 23:42.052
LET ME GUESS.
CORNELL.

23:42.054 --> 23:43.421
YEAH, THAT'S THE ONE.

23:43.423 --> 23:44.822
WE DON'T WANT
NO TROUBLE.

23:44.824 --> 23:46.590
WHAT CAN I GET YOU?

23:46.592 --> 23:47.825
WHAT DID WE HAVE
THAT NIGHT?

23:47.827 --> 23:50.594
TWO RUSTY NAILS,
PLEASE, SIR.

23:51.931 --> 23:53.247
¶<i> ROLL, RUDOLPH, ROLL</i> ¶

23:53.248 --> 23:54.564
I THOUGHT WE WERE GONNA
RE-CREATE EVERYTHING.

23:54.567 --> 23:55.800
YOU WEREN'T WEARING THAT.

23:55.802 --> 23:57.902
THE JACKET'S ENOUGH.

23:57.904 --> 23:59.637
ALL RIGHT, FORGET IT.

23:59.639 --> 24:02.173
I'M GONNA SET THE SCENE
FOR YOU, OKAY?

24:02.175 --> 24:03.941
Dave:
OKAY, IT'S PACKED.

24:03.943 --> 24:05.576
IT'S LOUD.

24:05.578 --> 24:08.746
LISTEN.

24:08.748 --> 24:10.448
WHAT DO YOU HEAR, MAN?

24:10.450 --> 24:12.483
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

24:12.485 --> 24:13.918
Woman: IT'S YOU.

24:14.821 --> 24:15.820
IS THAT --

24:15.822 --> 24:17.555
YEP.

24:17.557 --> 24:19.890
HEY.
NO, I'M SORRY.

24:19.892 --> 24:22.893
YOU HAVE SOME ISSUES.

24:22.895 --> 24:24.895
I WAS REALLY UPSET.

24:24.897 --> 24:27.665
LET ME BUY YOU
AN APOLOGY DRINK.

24:27.667 --> 24:29.033
OKAY.

24:32.505 --> 24:34.738
MY BUDDY AND I
WERE TRYING TO REMEMBER.

24:34.740 --> 24:36.640
I LOST SOMETHING
THAT NIGHT.

24:36.642 --> 24:39.510
OH, I HOPE IT WASN'T
THE PICTURE OF YOUR SON.

24:39.512 --> 24:40.945
WHAT?

24:40.947 --> 24:42.880
YOU WERE WAVING IT
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

24:42.882 --> 24:46.984
IT WAS THE STRANGEST THING
I'VE EVER SEEN IN A BAR.

24:46.986 --> 24:49.887
OKAY, MAYBE NOT.

24:52.825 --> 24:54.058
THAT'S MY BOY.

24:54.060 --> 24:56.527
Man:
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

24:56.529 --> 24:58.195
THAT'S AN ULTRASOUND.

24:58.197 --> 25:00.898
AH.

25:07.073 --> 25:09.273
THIS IS HOW I FOUND OUT
CHRISTY WAS PREGNANT.

25:11.210 --> 25:13.210
I NEVER
SHOWED ANYBODY BEFORE.

25:13.212 --> 25:14.879
Dave: OKAY.

25:14.881 --> 25:16.614
WAIT A MINUTE.

25:16.616 --> 25:19.250
SHE SHOWS YOU THE ULTRASOUND AND
THEN SHE GETS RID OF THE KID?

25:19.252 --> 25:21.752
NO, IT WAS EARLY ON.
WE DIDN'T PLAN IT.

25:21.754 --> 25:23.988
SHE DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT SHE WAS GONNA DO.

25:23.990 --> 25:26.023
I FOUND THE ULTRASOUND
AND CONFRONTED HER.

25:26.025 --> 25:28.692
THAT'S COLD, MAN.

25:28.694 --> 25:30.561
SHE WASN'T GONNA
SAY ANYTHING?

25:30.563 --> 25:32.997
SHE SWORE
SHE WAS ABOUT TO.

25:32.999 --> 25:35.232
I'M NOT SURE KNOWING HELPS,
ANYWAY.

25:35.234 --> 25:36.233
UH-HUH.

25:36.235 --> 25:38.569
SO, THIS IS A BABY?

25:38.571 --> 25:40.571
HOW THE HELL CAN YOU TELL
IT'S A BOY?

25:40.573 --> 25:42.873
YOU CAN'T.
IT'S TOO EARLY.

25:42.875 --> 25:46.110
CHRISTY'S BLOOD-TEST RESULTS
WERE MAILED TO THE HOUSE.

25:46.112 --> 25:47.878
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

25:47.880 --> 25:49.914
OH, NO,
I THINK IT DOES, BUDDY,

25:49.916 --> 25:52.983
BECAUSE YOU'RE SHOWING IT AROUND
TO THE WHOLE BAR HERE?

25:52.985 --> 25:55.686
YOU'RE CARRYING IT
IN YOUR WALLET FOR SIX YEARS?

25:55.688 --> 25:56.921
THAT'S PRETTY CREEPY.

25:56.923 --> 25:59.657
HEY, MAN,
THAT COP CORNELL,

25:59.659 --> 26:01.258
WHEN SHE CAME IN HERE,
WHO'D SHE TALK TO?

26:01.260 --> 26:02.860
EVERYONE.

26:04.263 --> 26:06.830
THEY TOLD HER I WAS SHOWING
A PICTURE OF MY SON.

26:06.832 --> 26:08.849
YEAH.

26:08.850 --> 26:10.867
AND SHE THINKS
THAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT TOM.

26:10.870 --> 26:14.872
THAT'S WHY SHE THOUGHT
I KNEW TOM WAS MINE.

26:14.874 --> 26:16.674
OKAY.

26:16.676 --> 26:18.175
YOU REMEMBER
WHAT HAPPENED NEXT?

26:19.612 --> 26:22.680
YOU KNOW, I-I'M --
I'M NOT A BAD GUY, YOU GUYS.

26:22.682 --> 26:25.616
I'M -- ALL I EVER WANTED
WAS A HOUSE,

26:25.618 --> 26:27.885
MY -- MY FAMILY,
MAYBE A DOG.

26:27.887 --> 26:30.020
CHRISTY HATES PETS.

26:30.022 --> 26:32.122
WHY DON'T YOU CALL YOUR WIFE
AND HAVE HER COME GET YOU?

26:32.124 --> 26:33.908
YOU KNOW WHY?

26:33.909 --> 26:35.693
BECAUSE IF I WAS CROSSING
THE STREET RIGHT NOW,

26:35.695 --> 26:36.860
I DON'T THINK SHE'D BRAKE.

26:36.862 --> 26:37.962
[ SCOFFS ]

26:37.964 --> 26:39.330
BEEN THERE.
I DON'T THINK SHE WOULD.

26:39.332 --> 26:40.965
WELL, WHAT'D YOU DO?

26:42.935 --> 26:44.902
IT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

26:44.904 --> 26:46.136
HMM.

26:46.138 --> 26:47.905
TROUBLE HAS
NO EXPIRATION DATE.

26:47.907 --> 26:48.973
[ SIGHS ]

26:48.975 --> 26:50.874
YOU'RE TELLING ME.

26:50.876 --> 26:53.677
[<i> MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING</i> ]

26:53.679 --> 26:55.713
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

26:55.715 --> 26:58.015
[ CELLPHONE BEEPING ]

27:02.888 --> 27:05.389
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

27:05.391 --> 27:06.390
[ Ringing ]

27:06.392 --> 27:07.891
SORRY. MY BAD.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

27:07.893 --> 27:09.126
<i> PLEASE LEAVE A MESSAGE.</i>
[ BEEP ]

27:09.128 --> 27:11.128
HEY, JESS, IT'S BEN.

27:11.130 --> 27:13.297
I-I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S
GONNA HAPPEN TOMORROW.

27:13.299 --> 27:15.032
UH, JUST...

27:15.034 --> 27:17.267
JUST WANTED TO SAY I'M SORRY.

27:17.269 --> 27:18.969
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

27:20.373 --> 27:23.173
I CALLED JESS TO WARN HER
THAT CHRISTY KNEW ABOUT US.

27:23.175 --> 27:24.942
EVERYONE KNOWS
AN ANGRY CHRISTY'S

27:24.944 --> 27:26.110
NOT ONE
TO BE TRIFLED WITH.

27:26.112 --> 27:27.945
BUT CORNELL
HEARD THE MESSAGE

27:27.947 --> 27:30.180
AND THOUGHT I WAS SAYING SORRY
FOR KILLING TOM.

27:30.182 --> 27:32.116
DO PEOPLE DO THAT?

27:32.117 --> 27:34.051
THEY CALL TO SAY SORRY
BEFORE THEY MURDER SOMEBODY?

27:34.053 --> 27:36.320
SOON, THEY'RE GONNA HAVE
GREETING CARDS FOR THE OCCASION,

27:36.322 --> 27:37.921
A GRIM REAPER
WITH SOME FLOWERS.

27:37.923 --> 27:39.256
"SORRY I MISSED YOU."

27:39.258 --> 27:41.425
YOU REMEMBER
WHAT HAPPENED NEXT?

27:41.427 --> 27:44.194
YEAH, IT'S FUZZY,
BUT THAT WAS THE...

27:44.196 --> 27:47.264
LOUD, OUT-OF-CONTROL,
GLASS-BREAKING PART, RIGHT?

27:47.266 --> 27:48.832
[ SNAPS FINGERS ]
RIGHT.

27:48.834 --> 27:51.068
AND THEN YOU MADE
YOUR GRACEFUL EXIT.

27:51.070 --> 27:52.202
THAT'S IT.

27:52.204 --> 27:54.371
I GUESS
WE'RE DONE HERE.

27:54.373 --> 27:55.406
UH, I'LL SETTLE UP.

27:55.408 --> 27:57.207
NO, NO, I GOT IT.
I GOT IT.

27:57.209 --> 27:59.376
DID YOU
COME INTO SOME MONEY?

27:59.378 --> 28:02.146
YEAH, I WON $25
ON A SCRATCHER.

28:02.148 --> 28:04.348
Man: LUCKY YOU.

28:06.052 --> 28:07.251
WAIT.

28:09.855 --> 28:10.921
HEY, MAN.

28:12.024 --> 28:13.190
WHERE TO NEXT, BROTHER?

28:13.192 --> 28:14.958
I GOT TO DO THIS PART
ON MY OWN.

28:14.960 --> 28:17.027
ARE YOU SURE?

28:17.029 --> 28:19.263
THIS WAS YOUR PLAN.

28:19.265 --> 28:21.331
YOU DIDN'T COME HOME WITH ME
THAT NIGHT.

28:21.333 --> 28:22.966
REMEMBER?

28:22.968 --> 28:25.736
OKAY.

28:29.709 --> 28:30.974
WHAT IS THAT?

28:30.976 --> 28:33.377
IS IT A TOOTH?

28:33.379 --> 28:36.447
THAT'S KIND OF SMALL,
MAN.

28:38.117 --> 28:40.050
OH, GOD.

28:41.921 --> 28:46.056
IT'S NOT...TOM'S,
IS IT?

28:51.931 --> 28:53.897
THIS IS A HUGE GAMBLE.

28:53.899 --> 28:55.032
YOU SAID THAT.

28:55.034 --> 28:57.501
ARE YOU SURE
YOU WANT TO DO IT?

28:59.305 --> 29:00.504
ALL RIGHT.

29:09.281 --> 29:11.749
[ CLICK ]

29:17.857 --> 29:19.974
WHY ARE WE HERE?

29:19.975 --> 29:22.092
YOU PRESENTED MY CLIENT WITH
A VIDEO FROM NOVEMBER 30th,

29:22.094 --> 29:24.027
THE NIGHT THAT TOM MURPHY
WAS KILLED.

29:24.029 --> 29:26.764
THE FOOTAGE SHOWS MY CLIENT
EXITING A TAXI

29:26.766 --> 29:28.966
AND WALKING TOWARDS
THE MURPHY HOME.

29:28.968 --> 29:32.202
AGAINST MY ADVICE, HE INSISTS
ON GIVING YOU A DETAILED ACCOUNT

29:32.204 --> 29:33.971
OF WHAT FOLLOWED.

29:33.973 --> 29:36.507
OH, SO, THE TAXI VIDEO
JOGGED YOUR MEMORY?

29:37.910 --> 29:40.511
NOT THE VIDEO.

29:40.513 --> 29:42.246
THIS.

29:52.892 --> 29:56.560
THAT APPEARS TO BE
A CHILD'S TOOTH.

29:56.562 --> 29:58.228
IT WAS TOM'S.

29:58.230 --> 30:00.297
AND YOU HAVE IT. WHY?

30:00.299 --> 30:03.300
I'LL GET TO THAT.

30:03.302 --> 30:07.070
THE REASON WHY I COULDN'T
REMEMBER ANYTHING THAT HAPPENED

30:07.072 --> 30:10.240
THE NIGHT TOM DIED
WAS BECAUSE I WAS DRUGGED.

30:11.343 --> 30:12.943
DIMINISHED CAPACITY?

30:12.945 --> 30:15.479
YOU CAN'T SERIOUSLY BE PLANNING
THAT AS YOUR DEFENSE.

30:15.481 --> 30:16.513
DEFENSE FROM WHAT?

30:16.515 --> 30:18.248
MY CLIENT
HASN'T BEEN CHARGED.

30:18.250 --> 30:20.551
WHAT WAS THE DRUG?

30:20.553 --> 30:21.985
BENZODIAZEPINE.

30:21.987 --> 30:23.987
MANUFACTURER
WARNING LABEL

30:23.989 --> 30:26.089
CAUTIONS THAT INTERACTION
WITH ALCOHOL

30:26.091 --> 30:27.891
CAN PRODUCE
NEGATIVE SIDE EFFECTS,

30:27.893 --> 30:29.426
INCLUDING MEMORY LOSS.

30:29.428 --> 30:32.830
IT'S ALL THERE, ALONG WITH
MR. LINDSEY'S SWORN STATEMENT

30:32.832 --> 30:36.200
CORROBORATING THE EVENTS
OF THAT EVENING.

30:42.308 --> 30:46.143
THIS WAS THE ULTRASOUND
I SHOWED THE PEOPLE IN THE BAR.

30:46.145 --> 30:48.946
OF YOUR SON?

30:48.948 --> 30:50.948
YEAH, BUT IT'S NOT TOM.

30:50.950 --> 30:54.918
CHRISTY WAS PREGNANT SIX YEARS
AGO, AND SHE TERMINATED.

30:54.920 --> 30:57.604
IT WAS A BOY.

30:57.605 --> 31:00.289
THAT'S WHY YOU THOUGHT
I KNEW TOM WAS MINE, RIGHT?

31:02.094 --> 31:04.328
THE JACKET I WORE
THE NIGHT TOM WAS KILLED

31:04.330 --> 31:06.363
I HAVEN'T WORN AGAIN
UNTIL YESTERDAY,

31:06.365 --> 31:08.298
WHEN DAVE AND I
RETRACED OUR STEPS.

31:08.300 --> 31:10.500
WHEN I PUT MY HAND
IN THE POCKET,

31:10.502 --> 31:15.339
THAT'S WHEN I FOUND THE TOOTH,
AND...IT ALL CAME BACK.

31:15.341 --> 31:18.308
YOU HAVE MY UNDIVIDED ATTENTION,
MR. CRAWFORD.

31:20.346 --> 31:24.114
I TOOK A TAXI HOME ALONE
FROM THE BAR.

31:28.087 --> 31:30.420
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

31:35.261 --> 31:37.427
HERE YOU GO, MAN.
THANKS.

31:39.164 --> 31:41.164
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

31:49.074 --> 31:52.175
THAT'S WHEN I SAW TOM'S TRIKE
IN THE DRIVEWAY.

32:19.204 --> 32:21.438
THE TV WAS ON,
SO I KNEW JESS WAS AWAKE,

32:21.440 --> 32:24.074
AND I WANTED TO WARN HER.

32:24.076 --> 32:26.109
WARN HER?
ABOUT WHAT?

32:26.111 --> 32:28.078
CHRISTY.

32:28.079 --> 32:30.046
THAT WAS THE NIGHT
SHE FOUND OUT ABOUT ME AND JESS.

32:30.049 --> 32:32.382
AND THAT'S WHAT YOU TWO
ARGUED ABOUT THAT NIGHT.

32:32.384 --> 32:34.051
YEAH, I WANTED TO GIVE JESS
A HEADS-UP

32:34.053 --> 32:35.419
BEFORE CHRISTY
CONFRONTED HER.

32:35.421 --> 32:37.187
SO I TRIED TO CALL HER
FROM THE BAR,

32:37.189 --> 32:38.722
BUT I DIALED
THE WRONG NUMBER.

32:38.724 --> 32:41.358
THAT'S THE MESSAGE
YOU HEARD.

32:41.360 --> 32:43.527
SO, I GO AROUND
TO THE BACK OF THE HOUSE.

32:43.529 --> 32:45.529
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

33:27.673 --> 33:29.239
[ FLOORBOARD CREAKS ]

33:31.710 --> 33:34.044
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

33:34.046 --> 33:35.779
HEY.

33:35.781 --> 33:38.048
Shh. Shh. Shh.

33:38.050 --> 33:39.082
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

33:39.084 --> 33:41.151
Your mom's sleeping.

33:42.421 --> 33:43.453
Here, come on.

33:43.455 --> 33:45.422
I'll take you
back to bed.

33:53.165 --> 33:55.232
I lost a tooth.

33:55.234 --> 33:56.500
You what?

33:56.502 --> 33:58.301
I LOST A TOOTH.

33:58.303 --> 33:59.536
YOU DID?

34:00.806 --> 34:03.540
HOW MANY OF THOSE THINGS
DO YOU GOT LEFT IN THERE?

34:03.542 --> 34:06.543
[ GASPS ]
THERE IT IS.

34:06.545 --> 34:08.345
WOW.

34:08.347 --> 34:12.082
I WOKE UP TO SEE
IF THE TOOTH FAIRY CAME,

34:12.084 --> 34:13.583
BUT IT WAS STILL THERE.

34:13.585 --> 34:14.785
YOU WORRIED?

34:16.789 --> 34:21.091
WELL, THINK ABOUT HOW MANY KIDS
THERE ARE IN THE WHOLE WORLD.

34:21.093 --> 34:23.193
HOW MANY
DO YOU THINK THERE ARE?

34:23.195 --> 34:24.561
A THOUSAND MILLION.

34:24.563 --> 34:26.096
A THOUSAND MILLION?

34:26.098 --> 34:27.264
[ LAUGHS ]

34:27.266 --> 34:28.765
THAT'S A LOT OF TEETH.

34:28.767 --> 34:30.434
SEE, THAT'S WHY
I WOULDN'T WORRY

34:30.436 --> 34:33.103
IF THE TOOTH FAIRY'S RUNNING
A COUPLE HOURS BEHIND.

34:33.105 --> 34:34.671
WOULD YOU?

34:37.376 --> 34:39.076
LET'S TAKE ONE MORE PEEK

34:39.078 --> 34:41.812
AND MAKE SURE THAT
THAT SUCKER'S STILL IN THERE.

34:41.814 --> 34:43.080
YEP.

34:49.288 --> 34:50.754
WHY DON'T I
READ YOU A BOOK?

34:50.756 --> 34:52.189
WHICH ONE DO YOU WANT?

34:52.191 --> 34:53.623
NO, THANK YOU.

34:53.625 --> 34:56.526
YOU DON'T WANT
A STORY, TOM?

34:56.528 --> 34:58.695
THOSE BOYS DON'T HAVE DADDIES,
EITHER.

35:01.233 --> 35:03.834
YOU KNOW, YOUR DADDY
LOVES YOU VERY MUCH.

35:03.836 --> 35:06.103
NO, HE DOES NOT.

35:06.105 --> 35:07.755
OF COURSE HE DOES.

35:07.756 --> 35:09.406
HE LOVES YOU MORE THAN ANYTHING
IN THE WORLD.

35:09.408 --> 35:11.875
WELL,
THEN WHY ISN'T HE HERE?

35:15.814 --> 35:17.447
HE WANTS TO BE.

35:17.449 --> 35:19.149
THAT'S ALL I KNOW.

35:21.854 --> 35:25.222
IF I HAD A SWEET, SMART,

35:25.224 --> 35:28.158
LOVING, HANDSOME LITTLE GUY
LIKE YOU...

35:30.696 --> 35:32.496
...THERE'S NOTHING IN THE WORLD
I WOULDN'T DO

35:32.498 --> 35:33.797
TO LET HIM KNOW
I LOVED HIM.

35:39.805 --> 35:42.372
[ GRUNTS ]

35:42.374 --> 35:44.541
GETTING SLEEPY, HUH?

35:53.318 --> 35:55.685
GOOD NIGHT,
LITTLE MAN.

36:23.682 --> 36:24.881
[ TV TURNS ON ]

36:24.883 --> 36:26.816
<i> WHAT'S TODAY,</i>
<i> MY FINE FELLOW?</i>

36:26.818 --> 36:29.686
<i> TODAY?</i>
<i> WHY, CHRISTMAS DAY!</i>

36:29.688 --> 36:31.588
<i> CHRISTMAS DAY.</i>
<i> I HAVEN'T MISSED IT.</i>

36:31.590 --> 36:33.657
<i> THE SPIRITS HAVE DONE IT</i>
<i> ALL IN ONE NIGHT.</i>

36:33.659 --> 36:34.758
<i> HELLO, MY FINE FELLOW.</i>

36:34.760 --> 36:35.759
<i> HELLO!</i>

36:35.761 --> 36:38.261
Cornell:
SO, YOU ADMIT IT.

36:38.263 --> 36:42.199
YOU WERE THE LAST PERSON
TO SEE TOM MURPHY ALIVE.

36:42.201 --> 36:46.236
NO.
THAT WOULD BE HIS KILLER.

36:46.238 --> 36:50.373
YOU'VE BEEN VERY THOROUGH,
MR. CRAWFORD.

36:50.375 --> 36:55.679
BUT YOU DO REALIZE THIS DOESN'T
ELIMINATE YOU AS A SUSPECT.

36:55.681 --> 36:57.948
I DON'T CARE.

36:57.950 --> 37:01.284
AND EVERYTHING YOU'VE SAID HERE
CAN BE USED AGAINST YOU.

37:01.286 --> 37:03.587
MR. GARNER
MUST HAVE TOLD YOU THAT.

37:05.257 --> 37:06.556
I DON'T CARE.

37:07.859 --> 37:09.492
WHY NOT?

37:09.494 --> 37:12.429
BECAUSE NOW<i> I</i> KNOW...

37:12.431 --> 37:14.598
I DIDN'T KILL TOM.

37:18.503 --> 37:21.238
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

37:39.024 --> 37:41.625
[ SIGHS ]

37:41.627 --> 37:42.959
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

37:46.665 --> 37:49.332
HEY, WHAT'S WRONG?

37:49.334 --> 37:50.967
IT WAS TOM'S TOOTH,
WASN'T IT?

37:52.838 --> 37:53.870
HOW WOULD YOU --

37:53.872 --> 37:55.939
YOU WOKE UP,
AND IT WAS GONE.

37:55.941 --> 37:57.540
AND THERE WAS A $10 BILL.

37:57.542 --> 37:59.509
SO YOU THOUGHT
IT WAS SCOTT.

37:59.511 --> 38:02.412
YEAH, I THOUGHT HE PUT IT
UNDER THE PILLOW

38:02.414 --> 38:04.881
WHILE I WAS SLEEPING.

38:04.883 --> 38:06.549
IT WAS YOU?

38:06.551 --> 38:09.386
I SAW YOUR LIGHT WAS ON,
AND I KNOCKED.

38:09.388 --> 38:11.821
THEN I WENT AROUND BACK,
AND THE DOOR WAS UNLOCKED.

38:11.823 --> 38:14.591
TOM WOKE UP,
SO I WALKED HIM BACK TO BED.

38:14.593 --> 38:16.893
I STAYED WITH HIM
UNTIL HE FELL ASLEEP.

38:16.895 --> 38:20.330
OH, BEN.

38:20.332 --> 38:21.865
I DIDN'T KILL TOM.

38:21.867 --> 38:25.402
I KNOW.
I KNOW THAT.

38:25.404 --> 38:26.836
[ CRYING ]

38:26.838 --> 38:30.006
I'M SO HAPPY
THAT HE WOKE UP.

38:30.008 --> 38:32.042
DON'T YOU SEE?
FOR HIS LAST NIGHT,

38:32.044 --> 38:36.579
HE GOT TO FEEL WHAT IT FELT LIKE
TO BE YOUR SON.

38:40.752 --> 38:41.818
[ SNIFFLES ]

38:43.422 --> 38:45.522
THANK YOU.

38:47.059 --> 38:49.459
THANK YOU.

38:51.697 --> 38:53.463
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

38:59.371 --> 39:01.338
[ CELLPHONE RINGS, VIBRATES ]

39:01.340 --> 39:02.839
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

39:02.841 --> 39:04.858
HEY.

39:04.859 --> 39:06.876
GARNER: So, I got home,
hopped on the treadmill,

39:06.878 --> 39:08.912
and suddenly,
it occurred to me.

39:08.914 --> 39:11.148
TO WIN THIS TRIAL,

39:11.149 --> 39:13.383
PROSECUTION HAS TO PROVE YOUR
GUILT BEYOND A REASONABLE DOUBT.

39:13.385 --> 39:14.684
Now, they can't do that

39:14.686 --> 39:16.986
if I offer an alternate theory
of the crime.

39:16.988 --> 39:18.888
OKAY, WHAT'S THE THEORY?

39:18.890 --> 39:20.657
You sleep with Jess once.

39:20.659 --> 39:23.026
NO ONE SAYS A WORD.

39:23.027 --> 39:25.394
THEN SIX YEARS LATER,
CHRISTY CONFRONTS YOU ON IT.

39:25.397 --> 39:29.099
AND THAT NIGHT, TOM IS KILLED
WITH YOUR FLASHLIGHT,

39:29.101 --> 39:32.769
LEFT IN A PLACE WHERE ONLY YOU
WILL DISCOVER HIM.

39:32.771 --> 39:36.906
WAIT, YOU CAN'T SERIOUSLY THINK
CHRISTY KILLED TOM.

39:36.908 --> 39:38.074
I don't know
who killed Tom.

39:38.076 --> 39:39.776
ALL I KNOW
IS THAT PAUSE YOU TOOK,

39:39.778 --> 39:41.811
THAT MOMENTARY HESITATION
WHEN YOU ASKED YOURSELF

39:41.813 --> 39:43.513
IF YOUR WIFE OF 17 YEARS
WAS A KILLER --

39:43.515 --> 39:46.483
IF I GOT YOU WONDERING
EVEN FOR A SECOND,

39:46.485 --> 39:47.884
THAT'S REASONABLE DOUBT.

39:47.886 --> 39:49.652
And the best part
is all this divorce crap,

39:49.654 --> 39:50.887
it's only gonna help.

39:50.889 --> 39:51.888
HOW?

39:51.890 --> 39:53.390
WELL,
SHE'S GONNA DESTROY YOU --

39:53.392 --> 39:54.791
LEAVE YOU ALONE,
BROKE AND PATHETIC.

39:54.793 --> 39:56.926
It's perfect.
It builds sympathy.

39:56.928 --> 39:58.495
That's no easy task.

39:58.497 --> 40:00.063
I'M NOT GONNA
LET HER DESTROY ME.

40:00.065 --> 40:01.564
How can you stop her, Ben?

40:01.566 --> 40:03.667
She's got money.
You don't.

40:03.668 --> 40:05.769
SHE'LL GET THE BETTER
ATTORNEY -- DIVORCE ATTORNEY.

40:05.771 --> 40:07.103
CHRISTY
DOESN'T HAVE MONEY.

40:07.105 --> 40:08.638
Well,
it turns out she does.

40:08.640 --> 40:10.907
THAT MYSTERY $25,000
THAT PAID FOR MY RETAINER,

40:10.909 --> 40:12.409
THAT CAME STRAIGHT
FROM THE MISSUS.

40:12.411 --> 40:13.660
Wait a minute.

40:13.661 --> 40:14.910
YOU SAID THAT WAS
A CASHIER'S CHECK.

40:14.913 --> 40:15.812
HOW DO YOU KNOW
WHERE IT CAME FROM?

40:15.814 --> 40:17.347
I work with criminals.

40:17.348 --> 40:18.881
I NEED TO KNOW WHERE
THE MONEY'S COMING FROM.

40:18.884 --> 40:21.851
JOHN, WE DON'T HAVE
THAT KIND OF MONEY.

40:21.853 --> 40:23.420
[ Sighs ]

40:23.422 --> 40:25.789
BEN, I'M A TWICE-DIVORCED
CRIMINAL ATTORNEY,

40:25.791 --> 40:27.424
AND THERE'S TWO THINGS I KNOW
WITH CERTAINTY --

40:27.426 --> 40:29.759
ONE, YOUR WIFE
IS HIDING CASH,

40:29.761 --> 40:32.796
AND, TWO,
THERE'S A LOT MORE OF IT.

40:32.798 --> 40:34.464
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK THAT?

40:34.466 --> 40:36.499
Given the way
she feels about you,

40:36.501 --> 40:39.836
DO YOU THINK SHE'D GIVE YOU
HER LAST 25 GRAND?
